(42, 7, 34, 40, 9, 11, 11, 'friend of publicans and sinners', 'Jesus and Sinners Connection', 'Both passages emphasize Jesus'' association with publicans and sinners, highlighting the criticism he faced. The Pharisees question why he eats with those they deem unworthy.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 7, 34, 43, 12, 2, 2, 'a friend of publicans and sinners', 'Jesus'' Fellowship with Sinners', 'Both passages emphasize Jesus'' association with those considered outcasts. In Luke, he is labeled a ''friend of publicans and sinners,'' while in John, he shares a meal with Lazarus, highlighting his acceptance of those marginalized by society.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 7, 34, 43, 2, 2, 2, 'eating and drinking', 'Jesus'' Social Engagement', 'Both passages emphasize Jesus'' presence at social gatherings. In Luke, he is criticized for eating and drinking, while in John, he is invited to a marriage, showcasing his role in communal celebrations.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini')
